{"ts":"2026-07-12T19:54:46.588Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-7dcf"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"S3: move the --allow-audit-* override flag family out of core command registrations into pm-governance-audit (enforcement stays core)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Remove core registration of the six override flags: --allow-audit-update + --allow-audit-dep-update (pm update / update-many; registration-helpers.ts:527-532, update-many.ts:59-60), --allow-audit-comment (comments.ts:41), --allow-audit-note, --allow-audit-learning (learnings.ts:33-35), --allow-audit-release (register-operations.ts:573). The package re-registers them via registerFlags(targetCommand) per D1 on pm-fg0b; core keeps the ENFORCEMENT (audit-protection guard) and keeps reading the option VALUES generically (anyOptionTrue alias lists + allowAuditBypass merge in register-mutation.ts:1376/1671/1714) so plugin-supplied flags pass through unchanged. Bare-core fallback behavior (D2): non-owner audit-gated mutations without the plugin per the decision (--force only vs hard block). Update error-guidance.ts:703 ownership-conflict guidance to be capability-aware (only mention audit flags when the plugin is installed — pm-qljv/pm-ulqu class, render from declared contract domain per the pm-mpbb ledger). Test risk: pm-qfdd commander-singleton leak affects in-process dynamic-flag tests — use worker-bridge suites (pm-kvd0 pattern). Blocked by the D1/D2 decision."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["bare-core","cli","governance","packages","refactor"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-12T19:54:46.588Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-12T19:54:46.588Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":150},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"no --allow-audit-* string registered by bare core (grep src/cli clean of flag registrations; option-value reads may remain); with package installed all six flags parse and gate exactly as today (covering specs); bare-core non-owner mutation error guidance no longer names uninstallable flags; MCP allowAudit* params follow the same ownership split (tool-option-contracts.ts:285-286)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-vjk3"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"1212979ccbe5de7c8fe8093d5889e0491a6df9235876e7e251e257c3ffa726dc","message":""}
